            "currentCldrName": "White Flower",
            "description": "<p>A stylized white flower. Generally depicted as a <a href=\"/rosette/\">rosette</a>-shaped <a href=\"/cherry-blossom/\">cherry blossom</a> in pink or red outline, often with a white fill.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apple, Microsoft, WhatsApp, and Facebook&#39;s designs feature Japanese characters roughly translating to&nbsp;<em>very well done</em>, used by teachers as a stamp for students who did exceptional work, often accompanied by a <a href=\"/hundred-points/\">score in red</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commonly used for <a href=\"/valentines-day/\">Valentine&rsquo;s Day</a>, <a href=\"/mothers-day/\">Mother&rsquo;s Day</a>, and other special occasions. May be more generally used to express such ideas as love, happiness, and beauty.&nbsp;Also used as a pink, white, or red&nbsp;accent color.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not to be confused with <a href=\"/cherry-blossom/\">ðŸŒ¸ Cherry Blossom</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"/hibiscus/\">ðŸŒº Hibiscus</a>, though their applications may overlap.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apple&#39;s flower <a href=\"/apple/ios-10.2/white-flower/\">previously</a> featured a red-outlined design, <a href=\"/google/android-5.0/white-flower/\">Google&#39;s</a> an orange outline. <a href=\"/microsoft/windows-10/white-flower/\">Microsoft&#39;s</a> flower was previously black and white, <a href=\"/samsung/experience-9.0/white-flower/\">Samsung</a> and <a href=\"/facebook/2.0/white-flower/\">Facebook&#39;s</a> pink and white.</p>",
